Sophia, however, is hopeful and wants her children to aspire to something greater than the life they have now. "But their upbringing is earlier than their mother�s. I would like my children, if they so wish, to go to a university and to obtain a higher education. I would be pleased if they grew over my everyday problems and my problems with my children. I want them to be strong. I want them to be stronger than me." She adds: "My new family consists of me and my two children. Any future earning will be theirs. I cannot do anything without them."

Sophia expresses her admirations for Portes. According to her, she does it with complete sincerity. In her upcoming Book �Eternal summer� Sophia will inform politicians all over the world, including the Bulgarian political elite, who live in other countries today, and especially her country, that she could not focus on herself. She did not want her children to remain children, who have been touched by this tragedy, but to become children, successfully realizing their projects and realizing their dreams. She incorrectly blames herself for leaving her children under this vision and not being able to protect herself from feeling �disappointed in herself � whenever she recalls her bad choice to leave her family.
